li.p:
Finally, we use extraction of roots to obtain
        x - 2 \amp =\sqrt{7} \amp\text{or}\amp\amp x - 2 \amp= -\sqrt{7}\amp \blert{\text{Solve each equation.}}
            x \amp =2+\sqrt{7} \amp\text{or}\amp\amp x \amp=2 -\sqrt{7}
    These are the exact values of the solutions. We use a calculator to find decimal approximations for each solution: 
        2+\sqrt{7}\approx 4.646~~~\text{and}~~~ 2-\sqrt{7}\approx -0.646
    These values are the x-intercepts of the graph of y=x^2-4x-3, as shown below.

webwork.pg-code:
Context("Fraction");
$p = Compute("-3/2");
$p2 = Compute("9/4");
Context()->flags->set( reduceConstants => 0, reduceConstantFunctions => 0,   );
$lhs = Formula("x**2-3x");
$rhs = Compute("1");
$lhs2 = Formula("x**2-3x+9/4");
$rhs2 = Compute("1+$p2");
$lin = Formula("x+$p")->reduce;
$rhs3 = Compute("13/4");
$r1 = Compute("3/2 + sqrt(13/4)");
$r2 = Compute("3/2 - sqrt(13/4)");
$answer = Formula("3/2 + sqrt(13/4), 3/2 - sqrt(13/4)");
$my_evaluator = $answer -> cmp(
 showHints=>1,
 showLengthHints => 1,
 partialCredit => 1,
); 
$answer2 = List("$r1, $r2");
$my_evaluator2 = $answer2 -> cmp(
 showHints=>1,
 showLengthHints => 1,
 partialCredit => 1,
  tolType => 'absolute',
  tolerance => .0051,
);

li.p:
Complete the square:
        p = \frac{1}{2}(-3) = \frac{-3}{2} ~~~\text{ and } ~~~ p^2 = \left(\frac{-3}{2}\right)^2 = \frac{9}{4}
        Add \frac{9}{4} to both sides of our equation:
        x^2 - 3x  \alert{{}+\frac{9}{4}}=\frac{5}{2}\alert{{}+\frac{9}{4}}

Finally, extract roots and solve each equation for x.
        x - \frac{3}{2}  =\sqrt{\frac{19}{4}} ~~~\text{ or }~~~ x - \frac{3}{2} = -\sqrt{\frac{19}{4}} 
        The solutions are \dfrac{3}{2}+\sqrt{\dfrac{19}{4}} and \dfrac{3}{2}-\sqrt{\dfrac{19}{4}}.

webwork.pg-code:
Context("Fraction");
$p = Compute("9/2");
$p2 = Compute("81/4");
Context()->flags->set( reduceConstants => 0, reduceConstantFunctions => 0,   );
$lhs = Formula("x**2+9x");
$rhs = Formula("-65/4");

$lhs2 = Formula("x**2+9x+81/4");
$rhs2 = Formula("$rhs+$p2");
$lin = Formula("x+$p")->reduce;
$rhs3 = Formula("$rhs+$p2")->reduce;
$answer = Formula("-$p + sqrt($rhs3), -$p - sqrt($rhs3)")->reduce;
$my_evaluator = $answer -> cmp(
 showHints=>1,
 showLengthHints => 1,
 partialCredit => 1,
);
